.TH "ima_kexec_cmdline" 9 "ima_kexec_cmdline" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ima_kexec_cmdline \- measure kexec cmdline boot args
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ima_kexec_cmdline
.BI "(int kernel_fd "  ","
.BI "const void *buf "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kernel_fd" 12
file descriptor of the kexec kernel being loaded
.IP "buf" 12
pointer to buffer
.IP "size" 12
size of buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Buffers can only be measured, not appraised.
